n\nREPLACEMENT OF REUSE WATER SERVICE STUBS. (\u00a7 8-2202)\n\nIn the event of the paving or widening of streets, or the raising or lowering of\nthe grade of a street, or in the installation of curbs or gutters and\/or\nsidewalks, or in the case of the installation of new reuse water lines initiated\nby the public, all reuse water service stubs may be replaced so as to meet the\nstandards prescribed by the City plumbing code. There shall be no charge for\nsuch replacements. \n(Ord. No. 2006-100, \u00a71, 9-19-06)\n"}